site_name: Queen Mary University Of London, 327 Mile End Road, London
description: T28 Prunus: - Dismantle tree in sections  T87 Mature multi stemmed Silver willow Tree - Carry out heavy reduction work to leave main stems at approx 9m above ground - Remove all lateral growth to minimise issues of encroachment.  T89g Group of Sycamore: - Remove stems growing towards building to ensure clearance of at least 3m.  2x Snake bark maples within garden at each student residence building: - Reduce back from building to ensure clearance of at least 3m.  T92 Semi mature Wild cherry: - Remove co-dominant stem growing towards building to ensure clearance of at least 2m.  T93 Semi mature Silver birch: - Remove small diameter branch encroaching towards building.  T95 Semi mature Winter flowering cherry: - Reduce back from building to ensure clearance of at least 3m.  T96g Group consisting 1x robinia and 1x Cherry within communal student residence garden: - Robinia: Reduce back from building to ensure clearance of at least 4m. - Cherry: Reduce crown overall by approx 2m in height and 2m in radial spread maintaining shape and form.  T97 Mature Robinia flanking student residence: - Reduce back from building to ensure clearance of at least 4m. - Remove all growth growing above building height to same clearance line to minimise debris fall onto building.  T98 Mature Snake bark maple: - Reduce back from building to ensure clearance of at least 2m. - Lift low crown to approx 3m. T99 Mature Whitebeam - Reduce crown overall by approx 2m in height and 3m in radial spread maintaining shape and form
